<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,696,941]" pageId="3" pageNumber="294">
The species was recently described based on a couple from Paraguay. Its general appearance is that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Martins, 1962" authorityName="Martins" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Microibidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exculptum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="294">M. exculptum</emphasis>
Martins, 1962
</taxonomicName>
, differing mainly by the darker antennae and by the erect setae on elytra distinctly sparser and shorter.
</paragraph>
